Erythropoietin (EPO) drugs market is segmented by product type, application, and distribution channel. Among the product types, Epoetin-alfa, Epoetin-beta, and Darbepoetin-alfa are the key segments driving the market. Epoetin-alfa is widely used for treating anemia in various conditions such as chronic kidney disease, chemotherapy-induced anemia, and HIV therapy. Epoetin-beta is another significant segment utilized for similar indications. Darbepoetin-alfa, a newer variant with an extended half-life, is gaining popularity in the market. In terms of application, EPO drugs find major usage in the treatment of anemia, renal disease, cancer, and other conditions. The increasing prevalence of chronic kidney disease and cancer is boosting the demand for EPO drugs in these segments. When considering the distribution channels, hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies play a vital role in reaching these drugs to the end-users efficiently.

