The Erythropoietin (EPO) drugs market encompasses various segments to cater to a wide range of applications and distribution channels. In recent years, the market has witnessed a significant shift towards the development and adoption of biosimilars, offering more cost-effective alternatives to biologics like Epoetin-Alfa, Darbepoetin-Alfa, and Epoetin-Beta. These drugs play a crucial role in addressing conditions such as cancer-related anemia, neurological disorders, hematology-related issues, renal diseases, and other indications. With hospitals, homecare settings, specialty centers, and various end-users in focus, the distribution of EPO drugs through hospital pharmacies, online pharmacies, and retail pharmacies has become essential for widespread accessibility.

